txt.en:
'It is just terrible! There are too many clumsy hands around at the Rovers' Yard, I think.

'In the past few weeks, I've seen more than a few crates end up in the waters of the harbour and these canals, and not even the Captain of the Haven seems interested in retrieving them. It is a disgrace, I tell you!

'If you can dredge up some of those sunken crates for me, I've some coin for you.'

Waterlogged crates can be found in the canals and in the harbour surrounding the Rovers' Yard in the Sail-haven of Umbar Baharbêl.\n\nGalyat has asked you to retrieve waterlogged crates that have sunken into the canals and harbour of the Sail-haven.
Retrieve waterlogged crates from the waters of Sail-haven ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Retrieved waterlogged crates from the waters of Sail-haven ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

'A-ha! Let's see what we have here!'

Galyat pries open one of the crates, and smiles.

'Everything seems to be intact, so as promised, here is your reward. It is the least I can do to repay you for your help, my friend.

'After all, [placeholder], I never did say these were mine!'
Deliver the waterlogged crates to Galyat

Galyat can be found near the Rovers' Yard to the east of the Harbour-warden's Tower in the Sail-haven of Umbar Baharbêl.\n\nYou have retrieved a number of waterlogged crates from the canals and harbour of the Sail-haven in Umbar Baharbêl. You should deliver them to Galyat.
In the bustle of commerce on the streets, markets, and piers of Umbar Baharbêl, it is not uncommon for goods to accidentally end up in a canal or at the bottom of the harbour of the Sail-haven.
